# nl-rag distilled facts — domain: matthew-hay
# one declarative sentence per line; load with:  neuron --db app.db import pack.facts --scope knowledge
[src:matthew-hay/30-31-vict-p01] This is a complete **list of acts of the Parliament of the United Kingdom for the year 1867**.
[src:matthew-hay/30-31-vict-p01] Note that the first parliament of the United Kingdom was held in 1801; parliaments between 1707 and 1800 were either parliaments of Great Britain or of Ireland).
[src:matthew-hay/30-31-vict-p01] For acts passed up until 1707, see the list of acts of the Parliament of England and the list of acts of the Parliament of Scotland.
[src:matthew-hay/30-31-vict-p01] For acts passed from 1707 to 1800, see the list of acts of the Parliament of Great Britain.
[src:matthew-hay/30-31-vict-p01] See also the list of acts of the Parliament of Ireland.
[src:matthew-hay/30-31-vict-p01] For acts of the devolved parliaments and assemblies in the United Kingdom, see the list of acts of the Scottish Parliament, the list of acts of the Northern Ireland Assembly, and the list of acts and measures of Senedd Cymru; see also the list of acts of the Parliament of Northern Ireland.
[src:matthew-hay/30-31-vict-p01] The number shown after each act's title is its chapter number.
[src:matthew-hay/30-31-vict-p01] Acts passed before 1963 are cited using this number, preceded by the year(s) of the reign during which the relevant parliamentary session was held; thus the Union with Ireland Act 1800 is cited as "39 & 40 Geo.
[src:matthew-hay/30-31-vict-p01] 67", meaning the 67th act passed during the session that started in the 39th year of the reign of George III and which finished in the 40th year of that reign.
[src:matthew-hay/30-31-vict-p01] Note that the modern convention is to use Arabic numerals in citations (thus "41 Geo.
[src:matthew-hay/30-31-vict-p01] Acts of the last session of the Parliament of Great Britain and the first session of the Parliament of the United Kingdom are both cited as "41 Geo.
[src:matthew-hay/30-31-vict-p01] Some of these acts have never had a short title.
[src:matthew-hay/30-31-vict-p01] Some of these acts have a short title given to them by later acts, such as by the Short Titles Act 1896.
[src:matthew-hay/30-31-vict-p01] The second session of the 19th Parliament of the United Kingdom, which met from 5 February 1867 until 21 August 1867.
[src:matthew-hay/30-31-vict-p01] An Act for the Union of Canada, Nova Scotia and New Brunswick, and the Government thereof; and for Purposes connected therewith.
[src:matthew-hay/30-31-vict-p01] An Act to repeal the Duties of Assessed Taxes on Dogs, and to impose in lieu thereof a Duty of Excise.
[src:matthew-hay/30-31-vict-p01] An Act for the establishment in the Metropolis of Asylums for the Sick, Insane, and Other Classes of the Poor, and of Dispensaries; and for the Distribution over the Metropolis of Portions of the Charge for Poor Relief; and for other Purposes relating to Poor Relief in the Metropolis.
[src:matthew-hay/30-31-vict-p01] An Act to apply the Sum of Seven million nine hundred and twenty-four thousand Pounds out of the Consolidated Fund to the Service of the Year ending the Thirty-first Day of March One thousand eight hundred and sixty-eight.
[src:matthew-hay/30-31-vict-p01] An Act for facilitating in certain Cases the Proceedings of the Commissioners appointed to make Inquiry respecting Trades Unions and other Associations of Employers or Workmen.
[src:matthew-hay/30-31-vict-p01] An Act to open the Professorships of Anatomy and Chirurgery, Chemistry and Botany, in the University of Dublin, to all Persons irrespective of their religious Creed; and to amend the Act 40 Geo.
[src:matthew-hay/30-31-vict-p01] An Act to amend the Law relating to the Duties and Drawbacks on Sugar.
[src:matthew-hay/30-31-vict-p01] An Act to facilitate the Recovery of Arrears of Alimony in certain Cases under Decrees and Orders of the Provincial and Diocesan Courts in Ireland.
[src:matthew-hay/30-31-vict-p01] An Act to amend the Law relating to Criminal Lunatics.
[src:matthew-hay/30-31-vict-p01] An Act for punishing Mutiny and Desertion, and for the better Payment of the Army and their Quarters.
[src:matthew-hay/30-31-vict-p01] An Act for the Regulation of Her Majesty's Royal Marine Forces while on shore.
[src:matthew-hay/30-31-vict-p01] An Act for the Abolition of certain Exemptions from Local Dues on Shipping and on Goods carried in Ships.
[src:matthew-hay/30-31-vict-p01] An Act for authorizing a Guarantee of Interest on a Loan to be raised by Canada towards the Construction of a Railway connecting Quebec and Halifax.
[src:matthew-hay/30-31-vict-p01] An Act to regulate the Court and Office of the Lyon King of Arms in Scotland, and the Emoluments of the Officers of the same.
[src:matthew-hay/30-31-vict-p01] An Act for the Preservation and further Protection of Oyster Fisheries.
[src:matthew-hay/30-31-vict-p01] An Act to authorize the Inclosure of certain Lands in pursuance of a Report of the Inclosure Commissioners for England and Wales.
